    "symptom": "The task dashboard doesn't re-render when tasks are added or completed. addTask and completeTask both return without errors but the UI stays frozen. TaskDashboard component only renders once on mount. hook useTasks seems to be calling the store correctly but there might be a memoization problem. IsLoading guard could be swallowing the update. something is preventing Zustand from notifying subscribers when tasks change.",
    "rootCause": "In-place mutation of the `tasks` array in `taskStore.ts:30`. Actions like `addTask` modify the existing array reference directly. Since Zustand's default equality check compares references, any update using the same array object (even if contents differ) is ignored, preventing `TaskDashboard.tsx` from re-rendering.",
    "codeLocation": "taskStore.ts:30",
    "evidence": [
      "taskStore.ts L30: tasks.push(newTask)",
      "taskStore.ts L38: task.completed = true",
      "taskStore.ts L46: tasks.splice(idx, 1)",
      "taskStore.ts L31: set({ tasks })"
    ],
